<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uqwade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qwade</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>h0x0r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>11/12/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>12:51:03 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class???</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">You can solo a wizard from 1 to 60 if you can handle the boredom.  at low levels you have to be very careful in choosing your fights because you dont get snare until 29.  Its possible to fight low blues and lvl but I always encourage people to seek groups when they can.  Its important to learn your role in a group from early on.</font><P><img src=http://clarussomnium.com/images/qwadesig2.jpg><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uwilleycoyote.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Willey Coyote</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.hotyellow98.com/mystwalker/tao.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>w4nn4b3!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>11/12/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>7:57:43 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.blizzard.com/images/broodwar/popup/lurker.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class???</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Thanks for the reply and I will clarify my situation. I have a lev 35 warrior that I cant stand to play. I just dont like how they cant really do anything but take damage and they cant even do that very well (alwais need a cleric around to survive even a blue mob). I also hated the fact that good groups are far and few between. I think that I made a fairly good warrior but really there is not much to it. I could pull very well, Pulling every mob in Cazic to the CY in groups no bigger then 2 or 3 is quite a feat but can be done if you know what you are doing. I just cant stand doing that because I know that when I play my brothers monk I can do the same thing without any effort at all. <br>
<br>
I started the wizard because of the versitility that I saw in the style of play. They seem to be very nice to have in a group and yet can still solo if need be. <br>
<br>
So far I have learned that Root never sticks when you want it to and that when Im in a group I cant just chain cast big DD spells and not get agroed.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I like the grouping aspect of being a wizard so far and have yet to learn all the tricks, but I am willing to learn and be the best that I can be at playing my class. <br>
<br>
I do however have a question on AoE spells and how they should be used in a group. If the chanter is mezzing and the tanks are killing one at a time If i cast a AoE spell the entire group of mobs agro me and everyone gets pissed off because I have upset the way they do things (despite the fact that I did 400 pts of damage with 100 mana). Is it really that hard for the chanter to re mez the mobs or to stun them while i cast another? Please tell me if anyone has used AoE spells in a group to a good effect.</font><P><font face="Lucida Handwriting" size="3"><b>Willey Coyote / Yensid</b></font><br>
Proud Officer of <b><i><font color="#800000"> Sacred Valor-</b></font><br>-When the going gets tough, the tank goes linkdead</font><i></b>

<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukinoel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinoel</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/favreaumat/boardicon.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>h0x0r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>11/14/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>10:31:54 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class???</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hehe, you found out already that root is unreliable at best, and very dangerous at worst. It can save your butt and give you enough time to run away, or kill you if you rely on it to be able to finish a mob.<br>
<br>
As for AoEs, that tactic isnt very used until 45+ and even then... I'm 50 now and never used it. I guess you can teach a Chanter that tactic, but I never took the time to do so.<br>
<br>
As for soloing, we do not solo very effectively until lvl 29, when we get our AoE snare (note that it's an AoE, be careful when you cast it, or it could bring you more than you bargained for, or you can get caught in it yourself). And even then, it's hard if you dont have SoW from one source or another or JBoots.<br>
<br>
You are right in the fact that wizzies are versatile. There are many ways to play a wizzie, unlike many ppl tend to believe. But your style of play will most likely be dictated on your group makeup than your personal tastes. Though there are variations to every wizzie's style of play in any given situation, they are still pretty similar as far as I could observe.<br>
<br>
A good wizzie can do crowd control. I saved my group's chanter or healer so many times with a quick root and a small /g MOVE! that I care to remember. Root can also be used to make a mob switch target. A rooted mob will always attack the character closest to it, so if one of your tanks gets low on life and the healer is low on mana, root the thing and have the higher life tank get closer. My usual group is aware of that, and when they see the little green spell effect, they know what to do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Wizzies are a blast to play, but sadly, many groups consider us as dead weight at higher lvls, because they only see the fact that we can dish out dmg but then need to med forever. But in a well balanced group, med time is minimal, as we usually only need to throw 1-2 nukes per mob and we sit and med for the remainder of the fight. We have to teach ppl, and not let our reputation be tarnished by over casting wizzies.</font><P><P><p align="center"><font color="#FF6600">
<b>Kinoel Feuerfaust </font></b><br>
Glass Cannon Extraordinaire<br><br>
<i>Secretary</i><br>
