<FONT FACE="Celtic" COLOR="#FF9900" SIZE=4>No, not all DE casters are Necros</font></p><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umystiquedekami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MystiqueDeKami</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>11/16/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>3:35:45 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class???</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I didn't solo any for xp after lev 12 but I've been messing aroundlast few levs (54-56) nad I found a pretty cool fact:  we canAE kite raptors.  At 54 I kited 4 of them at a time (use Columnof ___ ).  I'm pretty sure now (at 56) I could take 5, but sinceI hate soloing and TD ia really out of the way zone for a wizI didn't go back to test.  Also at 55 I could solo brownie guardsusing a druid slave on 2nd comp for harmony.  So I'd say evenpos 50 soloing is possible, just need to find the right placesand have the right equipment (jboots).  Tho personally I'd ratherplay my twink than solo if I can't get a group. <!--EZCODE EMOTICONSTART :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarkainosgrimlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkainos Grimlore</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>n00b!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>12/1/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>1:30:59 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class??? heck yeah they can</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Just dropping in my 2 coppers...<br>
<br>
  I was a grouper pretty much from day 1 with more emphasis on soloing after 35th lvl,  that's when I felt I could trust my snare  ( still let's me down every now n then).  Dont underestimate your stun spell,  comes in handy both for grping n soloing.  Soloing scenario - Snare resisted and mob is mad, stun asap...backup and decide &quot;root n run&quot; or retry snare.  Grping scenario  - MoB tries to frenchkiss healer/enchanter/ or even you  stun and decide if root is needed.<br>
<br>
  I'll start out soloing in a zone and if a group forms that I feel comfortable with I'll make an effort to join.  We've all had the &quot;bad&quot; grps and it's great to know that I can simply solo and wait for something else to come along.   I do not solo in dungeons...no room to kite, too strong a chance for trains.  <br>
<br>
 Qwade is right, you need group skills if you plan on Planes/Dragons/Dungeons with loot.  Learn the health bars of the mobs yer fighting,  how much dmg are yer grpmates avg, watch when they cast....when can you nuke without turning into overburn....and for pete's sake don't run when you do get an overburn.  Be a man and give the tanks a chance.  Don't get the killshot,  that's wasted mana...the idea is to tame it and let the tanks do the rest.<br>
<br>
  The only AE I've ever used grping was Grav flux...and that was only we had an awsome grp and I wanted to relieve some boredom.....major fun watching the tanks when the mob shoots up in the air.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Aww hell, I've rambled....deepest apologies...yes Wizards can solo, and quite nicely too!<br>
