<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uxyntic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xyntic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>n00b!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>12/29/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>7:45:15 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://members.home.net/nickelle/Xyn1sm.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class??? heck yeah they can</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I use AoE spells in nearly every fight.  Tears of Druzzil on any single pull.  I just love the 3 waves of 645 damage.  Even with multiple pulls, you can effectivley use AE spells if you have a good working relationship with the enchanter.  Timing is of the utmost concern and one mistake means big trouble.  Knowing cast times and recycle times is very important.<br>
If my AE spell takes 5 seconds to cast and the enchanters AE stun takes 3 seconds to cast, I begin my casting and the enchanter counts off 2.5 seconds to begin his AE stun.  That way, the moment my AE hits and draws aggro, the enchanter's stun spell hits.  The enchanter can begin mezzing and I can keep the others stunned with Tishan's Clash or whatever stuns I have loaded.  Meanwhile, the rest of the group has nearly dropped the first mob an the others are already weakened.<br>
Unfortunately, this doesn't happen alot.  We usually just end up with single pulls and I throw on Tears of Druzzil, but knowing what can be done if needed helps alot.</font><P><font face="Tempus Sans ITC"><font color="#999999"><fontsize=-2>________________________</font></font></font></b>
