<BR>
<img src="http://www.crosswinds.net/~raiyvenmoon/New1.jpg" width="250" height="113"><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uwizardzapinsommaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wizard Zapin Sommaz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/icon.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>n00b!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>2/22/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>12:18:13 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/Zapin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class??? heck yeah they can</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Soloing is good especially after 51 when the quad kiting exp and loot is great.  Groups are preferable though due to the greater amount of action and variety, not to mention that we can't solo where the coolest items drop.  Never rule out solo as an option or there will be times where you will get very discouraged because you can't get in a group.  I like outdoor groups with a snarer in the party.  Heh it is really easy for a Wizard to agro a mob and lead it in circles while tanks hack at it without taking damage.  In dungeons at later levels you will find that you just do just enuf damage not to agro mobs, stun, root, snare if nobody else can, and evac when things get scary.  To say that we do not add to the effectiveness of a group at later levels is not true, but it is a fact that many other classes will alway be more sought after for their superior group abilities than Wizards.  So when those damn groups are shouting HEALER or TANK or ENCHANTER, we can always do the solo thing for awhile. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><br> <p><b>Zapin Sommaz<BR>53 Wizard</b></p><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usloshieomygoshie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sloshie Omygoshie</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>w4nn4b3!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>2/22/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4:59:47 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class??? heck yeah they can</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I'm not an uber wizzie or anything,  but as far as I can tell we can solo,  just need to have sow/clarity to be worth it...and even then the down time is horrible.  I've<br>
been hangin out with another wizzie and we play ping pong,<br>
I snare and she nukes,  once it starts (slowly)  after her,  I nuke,  then she nukes,  etc etc etc.  If done properly neither of us takes any damage...because the aggro is always passed back and forth. We can so maybe 4 before we need to med,   usually 3.  </font><P><font color=purple>Sloshie Ohmygoshie Gnomish wizzie<br><a href=http://www.geocities.com/cavalri/ a><font color=purple>Order of the Ebon Tear</a></u></font><br><font color=purple>Level 36<br><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=53682 a><u><font color=purple>My Profile</a></font><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=laika>Laika</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>n00b!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>2/26/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>2:59:58 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Solo class??? heck yeah they can</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Wizards are definately a good and effective solo class, so long as you stick to low blue cons that wont resist too much and have few hit points for their level. I soloed alot in Ill Omen til around 30. From 35 to around 45 you can solo really well in Nurga, they even upped the xp modifier in that zone since i was there. post 51 is all Quad-kiting. I'm getting a bubble in 2 and half hours at lvl 53.<br>
